#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:5
msgid "Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:7
msgid ""
"The Scrapy settings allows you to customize the behaviour of all Scrapy "
"components, including the core, extensions, pipelines and spiders themselves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:10
msgid ""
"The infrastructure of the settings provides a global namespace of key-value "
"mappings that the code can use to pull configuration values from. The "
"settings can be populated through different mechanisms, which are described "
"below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:14
msgid ""
"The settings are also the mechanism for selecting the currently active "
"Scrapy project (in case you have many)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:17
msgid ""
"For a list of available built-in settings see: :ref:`topics-settings-ref`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:22
msgid "Designating the settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:24
msgid ""
"When you use Scrapy, you have to tell it which settings you're using. You "
"can do this by using an environment variable, ``SCRAPY_SETTINGS_MODULE``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:27
msgid ""
"The value of ``SCRAPY_SETTINGS_MODULE`` should be in Python path syntax, e."
"g. ``myproject.settings``. Note that the settings module should be on the "
"Python :ref:`import search path <tut-searchpath>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:34
msgid "Populating the settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:36
msgid ""
"Settings can be populated using different mechanisms, each of which has a "
"different precedence:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:39
msgid ":ref:`Command-line settings <cli-settings>` (highest precedence)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:40
msgid ":ref:`Spider settings <spider-settings>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:41
msgid ":ref:`Project settings <project-settings>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:42
msgid ":ref:`Add-on settings <addon-settings>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:43
msgid ":ref:`Command-specific default settings <cmd-default-settings>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:44
msgid ":ref:`Global default settings <default-settings>` (lowest precedence)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:49
msgid "1. Command-line settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:51
msgid ""
"Settings set in the command line have the highest precedence, overriding any "
"other settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:54
msgid ""
"You can explicitly override one or more settings using the ``-s`` (or ``--"
"set``) command-line option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:59 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1521
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1585 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1612
msgid "Example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:61
msgid "scrapy crawl myspider -s LOG_LEVEL=INFO -s LOG_FILE=scrapy.log"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:66
msgid "2. Spider settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:68
msgid ""
":ref:`Spiders <topics-spiders>` can define their own settings that will take "
"precedence and override the project ones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:71
msgid ""
":ref:`Pre-crawler settings <pre-crawler-settings>` cannot be defined per "
"spider, and :ref:`reactor settings <reactor-settings>` should not have a "
"different value per spider when :ref:`running multiple spiders in the same "
"process <run-multiple-spiders>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:76
msgid ""
"One way to do so is by setting their :attr:`~scrapy.Spider.custom_settings` "
"attribute:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:79
msgid ""
"import scrapy\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class MySpider(scrapy.Spider):\n"
"    name = \"myspider\"\n"
"\n"
"    custom_settings = {\n"
"        \"SOME_SETTING\": \"some value\",\n"
"    }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:91
msgid ""
"It's often better to implement :meth:`~scrapy.Spider.update_settings` "
"instead, and settings set there should use the ``\"spider\"`` priority "
"explicitly:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:94
msgid ""
"import scrapy\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class MySpider(scrapy.Spider):\n"
"    name = \"myspider\"\n"
"\n"
"    @classmethod\n"
"    def update_settings(cls, settings):\n"
"        super().update_settings(settings)\n"
"        settings.set(\"SOME_SETTING\", \"some value\", priority=\"spider\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:109
msgid ""
"It's also possible to modify the settings in the :meth:`~scrapy.Spider."
"from_crawler` method, e.g. based on :ref:`spider arguments <spiderargs>` or "
"other logic:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:113
msgid ""
"import scrapy\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class MySpider(scrapy.Spider):\n"
"    name = \"myspider\"\n"
"\n"
"    @classmethod\n"
"    def from_crawler(cls, crawler, *args, **kwargs):\n"
"        spider = super().from_crawler(crawler, *args, **kwargs)\n"
"        if \"some_argument\" in kwargs:\n"
"            spider.settings.set(\n"
"                \"SOME_SETTING\", kwargs[\"some_argument\"], "
"priority=\"spider\"\n"
"            )\n"
"        return spider"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:133
msgid "3. Project settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:135
msgid ""
"Scrapy projects include a settings module, usually a file called ``settings."
"py``, where you should populate most settings that apply to all your spiders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:139
msgid ":ref:`topics-settings-module-envvar`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:144
msgid "4. Add-on settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:146
msgid ""
":ref:`Add-ons <topics-addons>` can modify settings. They should do this with "
"``\"addon\"`` priority where possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:152
msgid "5. Command-specific default settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:154
msgid ""
"Each :ref:`Scrapy command <topics-commands>` can have its own default "
"settings, which override the :ref:`global default settings <default-"
"settings>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:157
msgid ""
"Those command-specific default settings are specified in the "
"``default_settings`` attribute of each command class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:163
msgid "6. Default global settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:165
msgid ""
"The ``scrapy.settings.default_settings`` module defines global default "
"values for some :ref:`built-in settings <topics-settings-ref>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:168
msgid ""
":command:`startproject` generates a ``settings.py`` file that sets some "
"settings to different values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:171
msgid ""
"The reference documentation of settings indicates the default value if one "
"exists. If :command:`startproject` sets a value, that value is documented as "
"default, and the value from ``scrapy.settings.default_settings`` is "
"documented as “fallback”."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:178
msgid "Compatibility with pickle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:180
msgid "Setting values must be :ref:`picklable <pickle-picklable>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:183
msgid "Import paths and classes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:185
msgid ""
"When a setting references a callable object to be imported by Scrapy, such "
"as a class or a function, there are two different ways you can specify that "
"object:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:188
msgid "As a string containing the import path of that object"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:190
msgid "As the object itself"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:192
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:195
msgid ""
"from mybot.pipelines.validate import ValidateMyItem\n"
"\n"
"ITEM_PIPELINES = {\n"
"    # passing the classname...\n"
"    ValidateMyItem: 300,\n"
"    # ...equals passing the class path\n"
"    \"mybot.pipelines.validate.ValidateMyItem\": 300,\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:206
msgid "Passing non-callable objects is not supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:210
msgid "How to access settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:214
msgid "In a spider, settings are available through ``self.settings``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:216
msgid ""
"class MySpider(scrapy.Spider):\n"
"    name = \"myspider\"\n"
"    start_urls = [\"http://example.com\"]\n"
"\n"
"    def parse(self, response):\n"
"        print(f\"Existing settings: {self.settings.attributes.keys()}\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:226
msgid ""
"The ``settings`` attribute is set in the base Spider class after the spider "
"is initialized.  If you want to use settings before the initialization (e."
"g., in your spider's ``__init__()`` method), you'll need to override the :"
"meth:`~scrapy.Spider.from_crawler` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:231
msgid ""
":ref:`Components <topics-components>` can also :ref:`access settings "
"<component-settings>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:234
msgid ""
"The ``settings`` object can be used like a :class:`dict` (e.g. "
"``settings[\"LOG_ENABLED\"]``). However, to support non-string setting "
"values, which may be passed from the command line as strings, it is "
"recommended to use one of the methods provided by the :class:`~scrapy."
"settings.Settings` API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:243
msgid "Component priority dictionaries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:245
msgid ""
"A **component priority dictionary** is a :class:`dict` where keys are :ref:"
"`components <topics-components>` and values are component priorities. For "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:250
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"path.to.ComponentA\": None,\n"
"    ComponentB: 100,\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:257
msgid ""
"A component can be specified either as a class object or through an import "
"path."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:260
msgid ""
"Component priority dictionaries are regular :class:`dict` objects. Be "
"careful not to define the same component more than once, e.g. with different "
"import path strings or defining both an import path and a :class:`type` "
"object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:265
msgid "A priority can be an :class:`int` or :data:`None`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:267
msgid ""
"A component with priority 1 goes *before* a component with priority 2. What "
"going before entails, however, depends on the corresponding setting. For "
"example, in the :setting:`DOWNLOADER_MIDDLEWARES` setting, components have "
"their :meth:`~scrapy.downloadermiddlewares.DownloaderMiddleware."
"process_request` method executed before that of later components, but have "
"their :meth:`~scrapy.downloadermiddlewares.DownloaderMiddleware."
"process_response` method executed after that of later components."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:276
msgid "A component with priority :data:`None` is disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:278
msgid ""
"Some component priority dictionaries get merged with some built-in value. "
"For example, :setting:`DOWNLOADER_MIDDLEWARES` is merged with :setting:"
"`DOWNLOADER_MIDDLEWARES_BASE`. This is where :data:`None` comes in handy, "
"allowing you to disable a component from the base setting in the regular "
"setting:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:284
msgid ""
"DOWNLOADER_MIDDLEWARES = {\n"
"    \"scrapy.downloadermiddlewares.offsite.OffsiteMiddleware\": None,\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:292
msgid "Special settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:294
msgid ""
"The following settings work slightly differently than all other settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:299
msgid "Pre-crawler settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:301
msgid ""
"**Pre-crawler settings** are settings used before the :class:`~scrapy."
"crawler.Crawler` object is created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:304
msgid "These settings cannot be :ref:`set from a spider <spider-settings>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:306
msgid ""
"These settings are :setting:`SPIDER_LOADER_CLASS` and settings used by the "
"corresponding :ref:`component <topics-components>`, e.g. :setting:"
"`SPIDER_MODULES` and :setting:`SPIDER_LOADER_WARN_ONLY` for the default "
"component."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:315
msgid "Reactor settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:317
msgid ""
"**Reactor settings** are settings tied to the :doc:`Twisted reactor <twisted:"
"core/howto/reactor-basics>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:320
msgid ""
"These settings can be defined from a spider. However, because only 1 reactor "
"can be used per process, these settings cannot use a different value per "
"spider when :ref:`running multiple spiders in the same process <run-multiple-"
"spiders>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:325
msgid ""
"In general, if different spiders define different values, the first defined "
"value is used. However, if two spiders request a different reactor, an "
"exception is raised."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:329
msgid "These settings are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:331
msgid ""
":setting:`ASYNCIO_EVENT_LOOP` (not possible to set per-spider when using :"
"class:`~scrapy.crawler.AsyncCrawlerProcess`, see below)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:334
msgid ""
":setting:`DNS_RESOLVER` and settings used by the corresponding component, e."
"g. :setting:`DNSCACHE_ENABLED`, :setting:`DNSCACHE_SIZE` and :setting:"
"`DNS_TIMEOUT` for the default one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:338
msgid ":setting:`REACTOR_THREADPOOL_MAXSIZE`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:340
msgid ""
":setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR` (ignored when using :class:`~scrapy.crawler."
"AsyncCrawlerProcess`, see below)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:343
msgid ""
":setting:`ASYNCIO_EVENT_LOOP` and :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR` are used upon "
"installing the reactor. The rest of the settings are applied when starting "
"the reactor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:347
msgid ""
"There is an additional restriction for :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR` and :"
"setting:`ASYNCIO_EVENT_LOOP` when using :class:`~scrapy.crawler."
"AsyncCrawlerProcess`: when this class is instantiated, it installs :class:"
"`~twisted.internet.asyncioreactor.AsyncioSelectorReactor`, ignoring the "
"value of :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR` and using the value of :setting:"
"`ASYNCIO_EVENT_LOOP` that was passed to :meth:`AsyncCrawlerProcess."
"__init__() <scrapy.crawler.AsyncCrawlerProcess.__init__>`. If a different "
"value for :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR` or :setting:`ASYNCIO_EVENT_LOOP` is "
"provided later, e.g. in :ref:`per-spider settings <spider-settings>`, an "
"exception will be raised."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:363
msgid "Built-in settings reference"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:365
msgid ""
"Here's a list of all available Scrapy settings, in alphabetical order, along "
"with their default values and the scope where they apply."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:368
msgid ""
"The scope, where available, shows where the setting is being used, if it's "
"tied to any particular component. In that case the module of that component "
"will be shown, typically an extension, middleware or pipeline. It also means "
"that the component must be enabled in order for the setting to have any "
"effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:376
msgid "ADDONS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:378 ../../../topics/settings.rst:905
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:951 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1335
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1355
msgid "Default: ``{}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:380
msgid ""
"A dict containing paths to the add-ons enabled in your project and their "
"priorities. For more information, see :ref:`topics-addons`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:386
msgid "AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:388 ../../../topics/settings.rst:398
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:408 ../../../topics/settings.rst:421
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:430 ../../../topics/settings.rst:440
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:450 ../../../topics/settings.rst:459
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1326 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1366
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1395 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1693
msgid "Default: ``None``"
