#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:390
msgid ""
"The AWS access key used by code that requires access to `Amazon Web "
"services`_, such as the :ref:`S3 feed storage backend <topics-feed-storage-"
"s3>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:396
msgid "AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:400
msgid ""
"The AWS secret key used by code that requires access to `Amazon Web "
"services`_, such as the :ref:`S3 feed storage backend <topics-feed-storage-"
"s3>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:406
msgid "AWS_SESSION_TOKEN"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:410
msgid ""
"The AWS security token used by code that requires access to `Amazon Web "
"services`_, such as the :ref:`S3 feed storage backend <topics-feed-storage-"
"s3>`, when using `temporary security credentials`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:419
msgid "AWS_ENDPOINT_URL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:423
msgid "Endpoint URL used for S3-like storage, for example Minio or s3.scality."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:428
msgid "AWS_USE_SSL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:432
msgid ""
"Use this option if you want to disable SSL connection for communication with "
"S3 or S3-like storage. By default SSL will be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:438
msgid "AWS_VERIFY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:442
msgid ""
"Verify SSL connection between Scrapy and S3 or S3-like storage. By default "
"SSL verification will occur."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:448
msgid "AWS_REGION_NAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:452
msgid "The name of the region associated with the AWS client."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:457
msgid "ASYNCIO_EVENT_LOOP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:461
msgid "Import path of a given ``asyncio`` event loop class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:463
msgid ""
"If the asyncio reactor is enabled (see :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR`) this "
"setting can be used to specify the asyncio event loop to be used with it. "
"Set the setting to the import path of the desired asyncio event loop class. "
"If the setting is set to ``None`` the default asyncio event loop will be "
"used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:468
msgid ""
"If you are installing the asyncio reactor manually using the :func:`~scrapy."
"utils.reactor.install_reactor` function, you can use the ``event_loop_path`` "
"parameter to indicate the import path of the event loop class to be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:472
msgid ""
"Note that the event loop class must inherit from :class:`asyncio."
"AbstractEventLoop`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:474
msgid ""
"Please be aware that, when using a non-default event loop (either defined "
"via :setting:`ASYNCIO_EVENT_LOOP` or installed with :func:`~scrapy.utils."
"reactor.install_reactor`), Scrapy will call :func:`asyncio.set_event_loop`, "
"which will set the specified event loop as the current loop for the current "
"OS thread."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:483
msgid "BOT_NAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:485
msgid ""
"Default: ``<project name>`` (:ref:`fallback <default-settings>`: "
"``'scrapybot'``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:487
msgid ""
"The name of the bot implemented by this Scrapy project (also known as the "
"project name). This name will be used for the logging too."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:490
msgid ""
"It's automatically populated with your project name when you create your "
"project with the :command:`startproject` command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:496
msgid "CONCURRENT_ITEMS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:498
msgid "Default: ``100``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:500
msgid ""
"Maximum number of concurrent items (per response) to process in parallel in :"
"ref:`item pipelines <topics-item-pipeline>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:506
msgid "CONCURRENT_REQUESTS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:508
msgid "Default: ``16``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:510
msgid ""
"The maximum number of concurrent (i.e. simultaneous) requests that will be "
"performed by the Scrapy downloader."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:516
msgid "CONCURRENT_REQUESTS_PER_DOMAIN"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:518
msgid "Default: ``1`` (:ref:`fallback <default-settings>`: ``8``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:520
msgid ""
"The maximum number of concurrent (i.e. simultaneous) requests that will be "
"performed to any single domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:523
msgid ""
"See also: :ref:`topics-autothrottle` and its :setting:"
"`AUTOTHROTTLE_TARGET_CONCURRENCY` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:530
msgid "DEFAULT_DROPITEM_LOG_LEVEL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:532
msgid "Default: ``\"WARNING\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:534
msgid "Default :ref:`log level <levels>` of messages about dropped items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:536
msgid ""
"When an item is dropped by raising :exc:`scrapy.exceptions.DropItem` from "
"the :func:`process_item` method of an :ref:`item pipeline <topics-item-"
"pipeline>`, a message is logged, and by default its log level is the one "
"configured in this setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:541
msgid ""
"You may specify this log level as an integer (e.g. ``20``), as a log level "
"constant (e.g. ``logging.INFO``) or as a string with the name of a log level "
"constant (e.g. ``\"INFO\"``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:545
msgid ""
"When writing an item pipeline, you can force a different log level by "
"setting :attr:`scrapy.exceptions.DropItem.log_level` in your :exc:`scrapy."
"exceptions.DropItem` exception. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:549
msgid ""
"from scrapy.exceptions import DropItem\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class MyPipeline:\n"
"    def process_item(self, item):\n"
"        if not item.get(\"price\"):\n"
"            raise DropItem(\"Missing price data\", log_level=\"INFO\")\n"
"        return item"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:563
msgid "DEFAULT_ITEM_CLASS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:565
msgid "Default: ``'scrapy.Item'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:567
msgid ""
"The default class that will be used for instantiating items in the :ref:`the "
"Scrapy shell <topics-shell>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:573
msgid "DEFAULT_REQUEST_HEADERS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:575 ../../../topics/settings.rst:824
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:917 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1204
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1840 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1901
msgid "Default:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:577
msgid ""
"{\n"
