#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1171
msgid "DUPEFILTER_DEBUG"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1175
msgid ""
"By default, ``RFPDupeFilter`` only logs the first duplicate request. "
"Setting :setting:`DUPEFILTER_DEBUG` to ``True`` will make it log all "
"duplicate requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1181
msgid "EDITOR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1183
msgid "Default: ``vi`` (on Unix systems) or the IDLE editor (on Windows)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1185
msgid ""
"The editor to use for editing spiders with the :command:`edit` command. "
"Additionally, if the ``EDITOR`` environment variable is set, the :command:"
"`edit` command will prefer it over the default setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1192
msgid "EXTENSIONS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1196
msgid ""
":ref:`Component priority dictionary <component-priority-dictionaries>` of "
"enabled extensions. See :ref:`topics-extensions`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1202
msgid "EXTENSIONS_BASE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1206
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"scrapy.extensions.corestats.CoreStats\": 0,\n"
"    \"scrapy.extensions.telnet.TelnetConsole\": 0,\n"
"    \"scrapy.extensions.memusage.MemoryUsage\": 0,\n"
"    \"scrapy.extensions.memdebug.MemoryDebugger\": 0,\n"
"    \"scrapy.extensions.closespider.CloseSpider\": 0,\n"
"    \"scrapy.extensions.feedexport.FeedExporter\": 0,\n"
"    \"scrapy.extensions.logstats.LogStats\": 0,\n"
"    \"scrapy.extensions.spiderstate.SpiderState\": 0,\n"
"    \"scrapy.extensions.throttle.AutoThrottle\": 0,\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1220
msgid ""
"A dict containing the extensions available by default in Scrapy, and their "
"orders. This setting contains all stable built-in extensions. Keep in mind "
"that some of them need to be enabled through a setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1224
msgid ""
"For more information See the :ref:`extensions user guide  <topics-"
"extensions>` and the :ref:`list of available extensions <topics-extensions-"
"ref>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1230
msgid "FEED_TEMPDIR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1232
msgid ""
"The Feed Temp dir allows you to set a custom folder to save crawler "
"temporary files before uploading with :ref:`FTP feed storage <topics-feed-"
"storage-ftp>` and :ref:`Amazon S3 <topics-feed-storage-s3>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1239
msgid "FEED_STORAGE_GCS_ACL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1241
msgid ""
"The Access Control List (ACL) used when storing items to :ref:`Google Cloud "
"Storage <topics-feed-storage-gcs>`. For more information on how to set this "
"value, please refer to the column *JSON API* in `Google Cloud documentation "
"<https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/access-control/lists>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1247
msgid "FORCE_CRAWLER_PROCESS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1251
msgid ""
"If ``False``, :ref:`Scrapy commands that need a CrawlerProcess <topics-"
"commands-crawlerprocess>` will decide between using :class:`scrapy.crawler."
"AsyncCrawlerProcess` and :class:`scrapy.crawler.CrawlerProcess` based on the "
"value of the :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR` setting, but ignoring its value in :"
"ref:`per-spider settings <spider-settings>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1258
msgid ""
"If ``True``, these commands will always use :class:`~scrapy.crawler."
"CrawlerProcess`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1261
msgid ""
"Set this to ``True`` if you want to set :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR` to a non-"
"default value in :ref:`per-spider settings <spider-settings>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1267
msgid "FTP_PASSIVE_MODE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1271
msgid "Whether or not to use passive mode when initiating FTP transfers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1283
msgid "FTP_PASSWORD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1285
msgid "Default: ``\"guest\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1287
msgid ""
"The password to use for FTP connections when there is no "
"``\"ftp_password\"`` in ``Request`` meta."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1291
msgid ""
"Paraphrasing `RFC 1635`_, although it is common to use either the password "
"\"guest\" or one's e-mail address for anonymous FTP, some FTP servers "
"explicitly ask for the user's e-mail address and will not allow login with "
"the \"guest\" password."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1308
msgid "FTP_USER"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1310
msgid "Default: ``\"anonymous\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1312
msgid ""
"The username to use for FTP connections when there is no ``\"ftp_user\"`` in "
"``Request`` meta."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1324
msgid "GCS_PROJECT_ID"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1328
msgid ""
"The Project ID that will be used when storing data on `Google Cloud "
"Storage`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1333
msgid "ITEM_PIPELINES"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1337
msgid ""
"A dict containing the item pipelines to use, and their orders. Order values "
"are arbitrary, but it is customary to define them in the 0-1000 range. Lower "
"orders process before higher orders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1341 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1925
msgid "Example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1343
msgid ""
"ITEM_PIPELINES = {\n"
"    \"mybot.pipelines.validate.ValidateMyItem\": 300,\n"
"    \"mybot.pipelines.validate.StoreMyItem\": 800,\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1353
msgid "ITEM_PIPELINES_BASE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1357
msgid ""
"A dict containing the pipelines enabled by default in Scrapy. You should "
"never modify this setting in your project, modify :setting:`ITEM_PIPELINES` "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1364
msgid "JOBDIR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1368
msgid ""
"A string indicating the directory for storing the state of a crawl when :ref:"
"`pausing and resuming crawls <topics-jobs>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1375
msgid "LOG_ENABLED"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1379
msgid "Whether to enable logging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1384
msgid "LOG_ENCODING"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1386
msgid "Default: ``'utf-8'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1388
msgid "The encoding to use for logging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1393
msgid "LOG_FILE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1397
msgid ""
"File name to use for logging output. If ``None``, standard error will be "
"used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1402
msgid "LOG_FILE_APPEND"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1406
msgid ""
"If ``False``, the log file specified with :setting:`LOG_FILE` will be "
"overwritten (discarding the output from previous runs, if any)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1412
msgid "LOG_FORMAT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1414
msgid "Default: ``'%(asctime)s [%(name)s] %(levelname)s: %(message)s'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1416
msgid ""
"String for formatting log messages. Refer to the :ref:`Python logging "
"documentation <logrecord-attributes>` for the whole list of available "
"placeholders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1423
msgid "LOG_DATEFORMAT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1425
msgid "Default: ``'%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1427
msgid ""
"String for formatting date/time, expansion of the ``%(asctime)s`` "
"placeholder in :setting:`LOG_FORMAT`. Refer to the :ref:`Python datetime "
"documentation <strftime-strptime-behavior>` for the whole list of available "
"directives."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1435
msgid "LOG_FORMATTER"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1437
msgid "Default: :class:`scrapy.logformatter.LogFormatter`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1439
msgid ""
"The class to use for :ref:`formatting log messages <custom-log-formats>` for "
"different actions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1444
msgid "LOG_LEVEL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1446
msgid "Default: ``'DEBUG'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1448
msgid ""
"Minimum level to log. Available levels are: CRITICAL, ERROR, WARNING, INFO, "
"DEBUG. For more info see :ref:`topics-logging`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1454
msgid "LOG_STDOUT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1458
msgid ""
"If ``True``, all standard output (and error) of your process will be "
"redirected to the log. For example if you ``print('hello')`` it will appear "
"in the Scrapy log."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1465
msgid "LOG_SHORT_NAMES"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1469
msgid ""
"If ``True``, the logs will just contain the root path. If it is set to "
"``False`` then it displays the component responsible for the log output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1475
msgid "LOG_VERSIONS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1477
msgid ""
"Default: ``[\"lxml\", \"libxml2\", \"cssselect\", \"parsel\", \"w3lib\", "
"\"Twisted\", \"Python\", \"pyOpenSSL\", \"cryptography\", \"Platform\"]``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1479
msgid "Logs the installed versions of the specified items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1481
msgid "An item can be any installed Python package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1483
msgid "The following special items are also supported:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1485
msgid "``libxml2``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1487
msgid "``Platform`` (:func:`platform.platform`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1489
msgid "``Python``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1494
msgid "LOGSTATS_INTERVAL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1496 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1561
msgid "Default: ``60.0``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1498
msgid ""
"The interval (in seconds) between each logging printout of the stats by :"
"class:`~scrapy.extensions.logstats.LogStats`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1504
msgid "MEMDEBUG_ENABLED"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1508
msgid "Whether to enable memory debugging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1513
msgid "MEMDEBUG_NOTIFY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1515
msgid "Default: ``[]``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1517
msgid ""
"When memory debugging is enabled a memory report will be sent to the "
"specified addresses if this setting is not empty, otherwise the report will "
"be written to the log."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1523
msgid "MEMDEBUG_NOTIFY = ['user@example.com']"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1528
msgid "MEMUSAGE_ENABLED"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1532 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1549
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1563 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1581
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1598
msgid "Scope: ``scrapy.extensions.memusage``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1534
msgid ""
"Whether to enable the memory usage extension. This extension keeps track of "
"a peak memory used by the process (it writes it to stats). It can also "
"optionally shutdown the Scrapy process when it exceeds a memory limit (see :"
"setting:`MEMUSAGE_LIMIT_MB`), and notify by email when that happened (see :"
"setting:`MEMUSAGE_NOTIFY_MAIL`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1540 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1554
#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1572 ../../../topics/settings.rst:1589
msgid "See :ref:`topics-extensions-ref-memusage`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1545
msgid "MEMUSAGE_LIMIT_MB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1551
msgid ""
"The maximum amount of memory to allow (in megabytes) before shutting down "
"Scrapy  (if MEMUSAGE_ENABLED is True). If zero, no check will be performed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1559
msgid "MEMUSAGE_CHECK_INTERVAL_SECONDS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1565
msgid ""
"The :ref:`Memory usage extension <topics-extensions-ref-memusage>` checks "
"the current memory usage, versus the limits set by :setting:"
"`MEMUSAGE_LIMIT_MB` and :setting:`MEMUSAGE_WARNING_MB`, at fixed time "
"intervals."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1570
msgid "This sets the length of these intervals, in seconds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1577
msgid "MEMUSAGE_NOTIFY_MAIL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1583
msgid "A list of emails to notify if the memory limit has been reached."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1587
msgid "MEMUSAGE_NOTIFY_MAIL = ['user@example.com']"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1594
msgid "MEMUSAGE_WARNING_MB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1600
msgid ""
"The maximum amount of memory to allow (in megabytes) before sending a "
"warning email notifying about it. If zero, no warning will be produced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1606
msgid "NEWSPIDER_MODULE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1608
msgid ""
"Default: ``\"<project name>.spiders\"`` (:ref:`fallback <default-settings>`: "
"``\"\"``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1610
msgid ""
"Module where to create new spiders using the :command:`genspider` command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1614
msgid "NEWSPIDER_MODULE = 'mybot.spiders_dev'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1619
msgid "RANDOMIZE_DOWNLOAD_DELAY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1623
msgid ""
"If enabled, Scrapy will wait a random amount of time (between 0.5 * :setting:"
"`DOWNLOAD_DELAY` and 1.5 * :setting:`DOWNLOAD_DELAY`) while fetching "
"requests from the same website."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1626
msgid ""
"This randomization decreases the chance of the crawler being detected (and "
"subsequently blocked) by sites which analyze requests looking for "
"statistically significant similarities in the time between their requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1630
msgid ""
"The randomization policy is the same used by `wget`_ ``--random-wait`` "
"option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1632
msgid ""
"If :setting:`DOWNLOAD_DELAY` is zero (default) this option has no effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1639
msgid "REACTOR_THREADPOOL_MAXSIZE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1641
msgid "Default: ``10``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1643
msgid ""
"The maximum limit for Twisted Reactor thread pool size. This is common multi-"
"purpose thread pool used by various Scrapy components. Threaded DNS "
"Resolver, BlockingFeedStorage, S3FilesStore just to name a few. Increase "
"this value if you're experiencing problems with insufficient blocking IO."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1651
msgid "REDIRECT_PRIORITY_ADJUST"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1653
msgid "Default: ``+2``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1655
msgid "Scope: ``scrapy.downloadermiddlewares.redirect.RedirectMiddleware``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1657
msgid "Adjust redirect request priority relative to original request:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1659
msgid "**a positive priority adjust (default) means higher priority.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1660
msgid "a negative priority adjust means lower priority."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1665
msgid "ROBOTSTXT_OBEY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1667
msgid "Default: ``True`` (:ref:`fallback <default-settings>`: ``False``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1669
msgid ""
"If enabled, Scrapy will respect robots.txt policies. For more information "
"see :ref:`topics-dlmw-robots`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1674
msgid ""
"While the default value is ``False`` for historical reasons, this option is "
"enabled by default in settings.py file generated by ``scrapy startproject`` "
"command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1681
msgid "ROBOTSTXT_PARSER"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1683
msgid "Default: ``'scrapy.robotstxt.ProtegoRobotParser'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1685
msgid ""
"The parser backend to use for parsing ``robots.txt`` files. For more "
"information see :ref:`topics-dlmw-robots`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1691
msgid "ROBOTSTXT_USER_AGENT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1695
msgid ""
"The user agent string to use for matching in the robots.txt file. If "
"``None``, the User-Agent header you are sending with the request or the :"
"setting:`USER_AGENT` setting (in that order) will be used for determining "
"the user agent to use in the robots.txt file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1703
msgid "SCHEDULER"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1705
msgid "Default: :class:`~scrapy.core.scheduler.Scheduler`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1707
msgid ""
"The scheduler class to be used for crawling. See :ref:`topics-scheduler` for "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1713
msgid "SCHEDULER_DEBUG"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1717
msgid ""
"Setting to ``True`` will log debug information about the requests scheduler. "
"This currently logs (only once) if the requests cannot be serialized to "
"disk. Stats counter (``scheduler/unserializable``) tracks the number of "
"times this happens."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1721
msgid "Example entry in logs::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1723
msgid ""
"1956-01-31 00:00:00+0800 [scrapy.core.scheduler] ERROR: Unable to serialize "
"request:\n"
"<GET http://example.com> - reason: cannot serialize <Request at 0x9a7c7ec>\n"
"(type Request)> - no more unserializable requests will be logged\n"
"(see 'scheduler/unserializable' stats counter)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1732
msgid "SCHEDULER_DISK_QUEUE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1734
msgid "Default: ``'scrapy.squeues.PickleLifoDiskQueue'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1736
msgid ""
"Type of disk queue that will be used by the scheduler. Other available types "
"are ``scrapy.squeues.PickleFifoDiskQueue``, ``scrapy.squeues."
"MarshalFifoDiskQueue``, ``scrapy.squeues.MarshalLifoDiskQueue``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1745
msgid "SCHEDULER_MEMORY_QUEUE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1747
msgid "Default: ``'scrapy.squeues.LifoMemoryQueue'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1749
msgid ""
"Type of in-memory queue used by the scheduler. Other available type is: "
"``scrapy.squeues.FifoMemoryQueue``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1756
msgid "SCHEDULER_PRIORITY_QUEUE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1758
msgid "Default: :class:`~scrapy.pqueues.DownloaderAwarePriorityQueue`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1760
msgid "Type of priority queue used by the scheduler."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1762
msgid "Another available type is :class:`~scrapy.pqueues.ScrapyPriorityQueue`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1764
msgid ""
":class:`~scrapy.pqueues.DownloaderAwarePriorityQueue` works better than :"
"class:`~scrapy.pqueues.ScrapyPriorityQueue` when you crawl many different "
"domains in parallel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1772
msgid "SCHEDULER_START_DISK_QUEUE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1774
msgid "Default: ``'scrapy.squeues.PickleFifoDiskQueue'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1776
msgid ""
"Type of disk queue (see :setting:`JOBDIR`) that the :ref:`scheduler <topics-"
"scheduler>` uses for :ref:`start requests <start-requests>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1779
msgid "For available choices, see :setting:`SCHEDULER_DISK_QUEUE`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1783 ../../../topics/settings.rst:3
msgid ""
"Use ``None`` or ``\"\"`` to disable these separate queues entirely, and "
"instead have start requests share the same queues as other requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1788 ../../../topics/settings.rst:8
msgid ""
"Disabling separate start request queues makes :ref:`start request order "
"<start-request-order>` unintuitive: start requests will be sent in order "
"only until :setting:`CONCURRENT_REQUESTS` is reached, then remaining start "
"requests will be sent in reverse order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1799
msgid "SCHEDULER_START_MEMORY_QUEUE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1801
msgid "Default: ``'scrapy.squeues.FifoMemoryQueue'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1803
msgid ""
"Type of in-memory queue that the :ref:`scheduler <topics-scheduler>` uses "
"for :ref:`start requests <start-requests>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1806
msgid "For available choices, see :setting:`SCHEDULER_MEMORY_QUEUE`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1816
msgid "SCRAPER_SLOT_MAX_ACTIVE_SIZE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1818
msgid "Default: ``5_000_000``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1820
msgid "Soft limit (in bytes) for response data being processed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1822
msgid ""
"While the sum of the sizes of all responses being processed is above this "
"value, Scrapy does not process new requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1828
msgid "SPIDER_CONTRACTS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1832
msgid ""
"A dict containing the spider contracts enabled in your project, used for "
"testing spiders. For more info see :ref:`topics-contracts`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1838
msgid "SPIDER_CONTRACTS_BASE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1842
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"scrapy.contracts.default.UrlContract\": 1,\n"
"    \"scrapy.contracts.default.ReturnsContract\": 2,\n"
"    \"scrapy.contracts.default.ScrapesContract\": 3,\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1850
msgid ""
"A dict containing the Scrapy contracts enabled by default in Scrapy. You "
"should never modify this setting in your project, modify :setting:"
"`SPIDER_CONTRACTS` instead. For more info see :ref:`topics-contracts`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1854
msgid ""
"You can disable any of these contracts by assigning ``None`` to their class "
"path in :setting:`SPIDER_CONTRACTS`. E.g., to disable the built-in "
"``ScrapesContract``, place this in your ``settings.py``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/settings.rst:1858
msgid ""
